Time for tea.

Rangana Herath becomes the leading wicket-taker of the year again, with 60 wickets.

The target is 393, a breeze compared to what they were set the last time they played a Hobart Test.

Australia still in charge here, but are a bowler short, and up against an experienced batting line-up. Big effort needed from the home team's bowling.

Janaka Siriwardene: "WOW! Herath has done it only in 9 matches and with 7 five-fors and 2 ten-fors. What a performance! Has really taken it over from Murali."

Meety: "For what it's worth Sri Lanka's average 4th innings score at Hobart is 379!"

Bharat: "As the saying goes, "Cricket is a old funny game", Another evident why test match is better than other format. Hopefully we have a competitive game ahead."
